Lucio Malan (born 30 July 1960) is an Italian politician.
Malan was born in <a href="/wiki/Luserna_San_Giovanni" title="Luserna San Giovanni">Luserna San Giovanni</a>, <a href="/wiki/Turin" title="Turin">Turin</a>. He earned his BA in <a href="/wiki/Literature" title="Literature">Literature</a> at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Turin" title="University of Turin">University of Turin</a>, then he obtained a <a href="/wiki/Master%27s_degree" title="Master's degree">master's degree</a> in <a href="/wiki/History" title="History">history</a> at <a href="/wiki/University_of_Nevada_Las_Vegas" title="University of Nevada Las Vegas" class="mw-redirect">University of Nevada Las Vegas</a>, where Lucio Malan was also tutor-assistant.
Lucio Malan is member of the <a href="/wiki/People_of_Freedom" title="People of Freedom" class="mw-redirect">People of Freedom</a> Party. From 1994 to 1996 he was a deputy. Since 2001 he has been senator and secretary of the presidency of <a href="/wiki/Italian_Senate" title="Italian Senate">Italian Senate</a>. He is also a member of <a href="/wiki/NATO_Parliamentary_Assembly" title="NATO Parliamentary Assembly">NATO Parliamentary Assembly</a>.
Lucio Malan is a member of the <a href="/wiki/Waldensian_Evangelical_Church" title="Waldensian Evangelical Church">Waldensian Evangelical Church</a>.
From 1990 to 1998 he was guest speaker of Italian History and Culture at University Studies Abroad Consortium in Turin, Italy.
From 1998 to 2008 he has been the director of communications of <a href="/wiki/Forza_Italia" title="Forza Italia">Forza Italia</a> Party.
Some Italian newspapers have reported that Senator Malan took his wife as a secretary using public funds of the Senate.
.
